                    <snrange>1273511 and above</snrange>
                </engfam>
                <engfam>Green Diesel Technology&#174; Engine
                    <snrange>1312588 and above</snrange>
                </engfam>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This TSI bulletin addresses a 25% increase in standard torque values for International&#174;
                    in-line engines. All International&#174; in-line engine products from model year 2000 and later have
                    adopted the same common set of
                    <emph type="bold">standard</emph>
                    torque tables that are currently used on the International&#174; VT 365 engine. Some general notes
                    to keep in mind are as follows:
                </para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>This TSI increases all standard bolt torque values by approximately 25%.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>This TSI bulletin does not apply to any International&#174; in-line engines 1999 model
                            year or earlier.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Use these new standard torque values for 2000 model year and later International&#174;
                            in-line engines, unless special torque values are required per existing service manual.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Do not use chlorinated solvents on bolts and tapped holes. Visually inspect parts for
                            cleanliness and obvious defects prior to assembly.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Phosphate coated fasteners (new) do not require oil lubrication during assembly and torque
                            application. Reused fasteners, even if originally phosphate coated, do require a light film
                            of engine oil lubrication to threads and under head area for proper torque application.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Standard Torque Values</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To avoid engine damage, do not substitute fasteners. Original equipment standard hardware is
                        defined as Class 10.9 metric standard coarse thread bolts (Rockwell "C" 33-39), all phosphate
                        coated.
                    </para>
                </caution>
                <caution>
                    <para>To avoid engine damage, do not use this standard torque chart with other International brand
                        engines
                        <ftnote id="fN01">Exception: International&#174; VT 365 and International&#174; in-line engines
                            (model years 2000 and later) will share this particular standard torque table.
                        </ftnote>
                        or engines made by other manufacturers.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid personal injury, possibly death or engine damage, continue to use all special torque
                        values contained in the engine service manuals. This TSI bulletin applies only to the
                        replacement of standard torque values for 2000 model year and later International&#174; in-line
                        engines.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
